description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Consultant Microbiologist &amp; Infection Control Doctor&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a full time Consultant in Department of Microbiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a motivated and committed individual to contribute&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to the development of Clinical Microbiology and Infection services in a district general&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hospital which has successfully modernized its Clinical Microbiology service with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a complete refresh of the laboratory equipment. In June 30th 2020, the Pathology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;laboratories at L&amp;D and Bedford merged LIMS systems and the Viapath contract ended.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full business case was signed to consolidate Pathology services across the 2 sites and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bedford will be the hub for Microbiology under this full business case.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will form part of a team providing microbiology and infection&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;control services. It is intended that the appointee will have particular responsibility for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;infection control. The Trust has seen a dramatic improvement in infection rates in the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;last few years and is keen to appoint a candidate who can continue and improve on&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time for Bedford. Increases in the local population over the next ten&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;years will mean that the hospital will serve a community of over 500,000. The hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;will continue to develop its clinical capabilities to enable it to achieve national and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;international recognition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bedford is a thriving market town, which provides easy access to London (55 miles),&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the North of England and beyond through its rail links and M1/A1/A14 accessibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An informal visit may be arranged by appointment with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Simantee Guha, Consultant Microbiologist – telephone 01234 355122 X 4703&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Secretary – X 4611)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Fraser Mutch, Clinical Director of Pathology – telephone 01234 792325&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Secretary – 01234 792628)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 14th December&lt;/p&gt;
